  Complete Implementation

  Phase 4A: Schema & Core (Tasks 1-6) ✅

  1. EdgeMetadata evidence field - Added evidence: list[str] to EdgeMetadata dataclass
  2. Neo4j integration - Evidence stored as JSON arrays in Neo4j properties
  3. Evidence methods - has_evidence(), is_well_supported(), add_evidence(), get_citation_text()
  4. Helper functions - create_cited_metadata(), create_research_backed_metadata(), create_user_observation_metadata()
  5. Database migration - Script to add evidence field to existing relationships (/scripts/migrate_add_evidence_field.py)

  Phase 4B: Provenance Query Builders (Tasks 7-8) ✅

  Created 6 provenance query builders in /core/models/query/_provenance_queries.py:

  1. build_trust_filtered_prerequisite_chain() - Filter by allowed sources
  2. build_provenance_distribution_query() - Analyze source distribution
  3. build_ai_validation_queue_query() - AI relationships needing validation
  4. build_provenance_upgrade_candidates_query() - Auto-promote high-quality AI relationships
  5. build_well_supported_prerequisites_query() - Filter by evidence count (3+)
  6. build_citation_export_query() - Export bibliography for Askesis responses

  Phase 4C: Askesis Citation Service (Tasks 9-10) ✅

  1. AskesisCitationService - Service for retrieving and formatting citations
  2. RelationshipCitation - Dataclass for individual citations
  3. CitationBundle - Bundle of citations for a knowledge unit
  4. Askesis Integration - Citations automatically appended to responses when discussing knowledge units

